Class TreeModelFilter<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • it.unibz.krdb.obda.protege4.gui.treemodels.TreeModelFilter<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - T is the class name of the kind of object that is taken as input by an implementation of TreeModelFilter.
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    MappingFunctorTreeModelFilter, MappingHeadVariableTreeModelFilter, MappingIDTreeModelFilter, MappingPredicateTreeModelFilter, MappingSQLStringTreeModelFilter, MappingStringTreeModelFilter

    public abstract class TreeModelFilter<T>
extends Object
    An abstract filter that can be used by TreeModels to discriminate certain elements stored in the controller associated to the tree model.

        public abstract boolean match(T object)
        A matching function that returns true if the object complies to the internal logic of the Filter. Instances of TreeModelFilter should define their own logic.
        Parameters:
        object - The object that needs to be matches
        Returns:
        true if the object matches the internal logic, false otherwise
